[...] University of Oxford CPD Centre 2014-11-27T11:32:34+00:00 2014-11-27T11:32:34+00:00 University of Oxford Accredited Short Course: Essential Medical Statistics, 13-17 April 2015 \ufffd\ufffd\ufffd Limited number of places available https://www.jiscmail.ac.uk:443/cgi-bin/webadmin?A2=BIOINFORMATICS;ab7aaebc.1411 Learning about logistic regression, Cox regression, meta-analysis and more<br>This module is designed for health care professionals or graduate students who already have some research experience and an understanding of basic statistical principles, and who wish to develop their statistical expertise. Teaching is interactive and will emphasise the practical application of statistical methods to real-life problems, rather than statistical theory. Students will be able to explore and analyse data using a variety statistical packages.<br>Full details and information on how to apply can be found on the course webpage - www.conted.ox.ac.uk/ems
